snippet.textDisplay:
Hi guys! Absolutely love your videos! I've been wondering if you've ever seen 90s Sci Fi show Babylon 5? Sure the CG is heavily dated but for it's time there was no other show to use CG so extensively. The difference between season 1 and season 4 is night and day!
Also, Patricia Tallman who stared in the show was also one of the lead stunt performers on Star Trek TNG, I'm certain she would be more than happy to provide some insight into how a TV show was able to deliver such great FX and stunts for its day!

All the best guys
snippet.textOriginal:

snippet.textDisplay: I hope the VFX pros know how much we fans truly appreciate the countless hours of painstaking work they put into these movies.  I could have never imagined movies like the Marvel Movies in my wildest dreams growing up and always assumed comic book movies would just be old-school 2D animated.  Now they are animated, but in such an incredibly seamless way that they just look like real life.  I hope the VFX teams get paid really well because they are really as important to the quality of the movie as the actors.
snippet.textOriginal: I hope the VFX pros know how much we fans truly appreciate the countless hours of painstaking work they put into these movies.  I could have never imagined movies like the Marvel Movies in my wildest dreams growing up and always assumed comic book movies would just be old-school 2D animated.  Now they are animated, but in such an incredibly seamless way that they just look like real life.  I hope the VFX teams get paid really well because they are really as important to the quality of the movie as the actors.
